page.title: 08Dock Head-Southampton.
page.content: Our survey area included a part of {Southampton Dock-the Dock Head.} It is at the confluence of the Rivers Test and Itchen.There are warehouses and a grain silo on the dockside. {The Dock Head}serves mainly passenger liners.Many people used to travel from all over the British Isles to embark large liners to voyage to foreign countries from Southampton Docks but now there are very few liners left.Other shipping passes the Dock Head{(container ships},small coasters) and many small {pleasure craft}head up the Itchen and Test.
